node.text:
Video tour of The Syshaus designed by @studio.arthurcasas.

The Syshaus is the future of housing. It is a concept with constructive system with a standardized 1.2m grid system that allows the house to be built within 6 months. The keywords are quality, practicality, and sustainability, and eliminates the hassle of constructing a house.

In the vibrant Mexican city of Cancún, Donceles 8 is an apartment of grey nuances beautifully complimented by soft wood. With its split-level configuration, the apartment is encouraging exploration; especially for the four-footed friends. It is designed by @kiltropolaris + @juancarral + @wewi.__. // Photos by @cesarbejarstudio (image 4 by @fabianml)

node.text:
Who’d you bring? 😍
The Woodman’s Treehouse is a luxurious two-storey suite placed between and beneath the canopies of aged oaks. Situated in this beautiful landscape, the treehouse gives the impression of being one with nature and experiencing the natural environment first hand. With a timber construction, the treehouse draws on diverse architectural and cultural references – creating a rich and playful structure in the picturesque surroundings. The treehouse is designed by Keith Brownlie of @beam_architects and Guy Mallinson of @mallinsonswoodlandretreat. It is located in Dorset, United Kingdom. // Photos by @hvit.co.uk (image 2 by @haarkon_).

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Casa Lavra I is a minimalist home with clean lines and a softly nuanced interior. Part box home, part gable house, the building’s expression changes according to one’s perspective, creating a more dynamic range of volumes. It is designed by @nfc.arquitectura and is to be build in Lavra, Portugal // Visuals by @nrenders.viz.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
Who’d you bring? 😍
Botanique Hotel & Spa is a retreat nestled in a confluence of three rich river valleys, amid the picturesque hillsides of Mantiqueira Mountains. Surrounded by mid-tropical Atlantic forests, the retreat follows a “European borrowed” styling, introducing a contemporary appeal in line with its authentic feel. It is designed by @candidatabet, and is located in Campos do Jordão, Brazil // Photos by @tucareines.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
Knapphullet is a small cabin with amazing ocean views, and accessible through a small pathway. The house leaves a very little footprint minimizing impact, and focuses on minimal living with only the most necessary spaces available – enough to allow the residents to embrace the nature. The cabin is designed by @lundhagem and is located in Sandefjord, Norway // Photos by @ivarkvaal and Kim Müller.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

In Tulum’s newest living community, Villa Umán Ha (Mayan for “a passage of water”) is an upcoming stacked, sanctuary home with a warm and elegant interior. While the house has a modern character, it is proposed with local materials such as chukum to maintain the connection to the regional traditions. It is designed by @ubicuoo.studio for @zeptorealty.

node.text:
Dope or nope? 🤔
House in Kyoto is a courtyard home realized with a large columnless atrium in the center. Here, the owner has placed an open-air bathroom in the very middle of the house, as he loves taking a bath. From there, he can look at a beautiful indoor tree. Normally, trees need humidity, wind, rain, direct sunlight, etc., so the solution was to select a Ficus Benjamina tree needing much less. The house is designed by @architecture_studio_07beach and is located in Kyoto, Japan. // Photos by @yosukeohtake_archiphoto.

Swipe left! What do you think? 💚
Villa Noi Phang Nga is a large 1880 sqm. ocean-front residence, which can accommodate both friends and family for a collective getaway. With glass panels covering most of the oceanfront side of the house, the home aims at connectivity to nature, i.e. the beach and the sea. The house is designed by @duangritbunnag and is located in Phangnga, Thailand // Photo courtesy of @duangritbunnag.

node.text:
Who’d you bring? 😍
Perched high among the trees with breathtaking views of the hidden lake and wildflower meadows, MetalLark Tower is the perfect getaway. With its two-storey layout, the 800 sq. ft. cabin’s ground floor consists of one king bed, one hide-away bunk bed, and one bathroom whereas the second floor includes the living area, high up to give the guests a bird’s eye view of the incredible surroundings. MetalLark Tower by @nordlyslodgingco is located in Frederic, Wisconsin. // Photos by @levimkelly.

The house is designed by @iconcast.lk and is located in Malabe, Sri Lanka. // Photos by @ganidubalasuriya.

Thoughts on this concept? 🤔
La Casa Que Canta is a futuristically designed two-storey residence with views towards the Costa Jama Beach in Ecuador. With its curved lines and deck-like interior, the house resembles the style of a modern ship scouting the ocean from its front row position. The concept is designed by @castroarquitetos.
